channel.title: ASF Jira
channel.description: This file is an XML representation of an issue

item.title: [HIVE-22505] ClassCastException caused by wrong Vectorized operator selection
item.description:
VectorMapJoinOuterFilteredOperator does not currently support full outer joins but using the current Vectorizer logic it can be selected when a there is a filter involved. This can make queries fail with ClassCastException when their data and metadata in the VectorMapJoinOuterFilteredOperator do not match.

The query attached demonstrates the issue and the log attached shows the java.lang.ClassCastException
item.summary: ClassCastException caused by wrong Vectorized operator selection

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.

comments.comment:
Attaching a patch that modifies the Vectorizer to make sure that VectorMapJoinOuterFilteredOperator is not selected for non-supported full-outer joins. Instead it falls back to a non-vectorized implementation.

Also attaching a test query to test the particular scenario
